      <p>The third set of simulated reads was drawn from version 2.0 of the genome of the wheat‐pathogenic, ascomycete fungus <italic toggle="yes">Zymoseptoria tritici</italic> (Goodwin et al., <xref rid="men13580-bib-0015" ref-type="bibr">2011</xref>), which was downloaded from the Joint Genome Institute of the U.S. Department of Energy (<ext-link xlink:href="https://mycocosm.jgi.doe.gov/Mycgr3/Mycgr3.home.html" ext-link-type="uri">https://mycocosm.jgi.doe.gov/Mycgr3/Mycgr3.home.html</ext-link>). Simulated long reads were produced in the same way as for wheat and assembled with <sc>unicycler</sc>. Ten homologous protein query sequences were downloaded from the GenBank nr database (Clark et al., <xref rid="men13580-bib-0010" ref-type="bibr">2016</xref>) and are listed in Table <xref rid="men13580-tbl-0002" ref-type="table">2</xref>. These simulations demonstrated the behaviour of <sc>slag</sc> with a simple, relatively nonrepetitive genome. Assembly accuracy for the second and third simulated sets was measured by percentage identities in <sc>blastn</sc> output from contigs against the relevant reference genome.</p>
