            <p>Column headings B73, fStanley, hStanley and qStanley refer respectively to the read sets from maize “B73” and the full, half and quarter read sets from wheat “Stanley.” The enzymes are given in Table <xref rid="men13580-tbl-0003" ref-type="table">3</xref>. All rows below the first are means over the number of runs given in the first row. Percentage match refers to contig identity with the B73 or Chinese Spring reference genomes. Memory is the maximum at any point during the run.</p>
          </fn>
